\fs24 \cf4 \strokec4 8. Variable-importance method\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \cb3 \strokec4 The study primarily utilized 
\f2\b permutation importance
\f0\b0  and 
\f2\b partial dependence sensitivity analysis
\f0\b0  to evaluate the relationships between environmental predictors and carbon concentrations,.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf4 \cb3 Variable-Importance Methods\cf4 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa120\partightenfactor0
\ls12\ilvl0\cf4 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 Permutation Importance:
\f0\b0  This was the primary metric used to rank the underlying determinants of PIC and POC variability. It was defined as the error (Root Mean Squared Error, or RMSE) generated when a single variable is permuted, while others are held at their observed values,.\cb1 \
\ls12\ilvl0
\f2\b \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 Partial Dependence Plots (PDPs):
\f0\b0  These were used to visualize the nonlinear sensitivity of the carbon pools to individual environmental parameters across their observed range,.\cb1 \
\ls12\ilvl0
\f2\b \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 Median Replacement Analysis:
\f0\b0  The authors also employed a diagnostic method where they compared the full model prediction to a prediction where a specific variable was replaced by its 
\f2\b global median
\f0\b0 ,. This allowed them to map the spatial and temporal impacts of individual drivers.
\fs28 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs24 \cf4 \cb3 \strokec4 Data Usage for Importance\cf4 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa120\partightenfactor0
\ls13\ilvl0\cf4 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 Held-out Data:
\f0\b0  The permutation importance was explicitly computed on the 
\f2\b testing data set
\f0\b0 ,. The importance values were then normalized by the standard deviation of the target data from each data set to allow for comparison between PIC and POC.
\fs28 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs24 \cf4 \cb3 \strokec4 Handling of Correlated Predictors\cf4 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf4 \cb3 \strokec4 The researchers acknowledged that environmental fields 
\f2\b covary
\f0\b0  significantly in the natural ocean,.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa120\partightenfactor0
\ls14\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf4 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 Scientific Framework:
\f0\b0  They addressed this by framing their results as "
\f2\b apparent relationships
\f0\b0 "\'97those emerging from a complex environment where multiple drivers interact and covary\'97rather than the "intrinsic physiological relationships" established in controlled laboratory settings.\cb1 \
\ls14\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 \
\ls14\ilvl0
\f2\b \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 Technical Mitigation:
\f0\b0  To handle these correlations statistically, the authors cited 
\f2\b Strobl et al. (2008)
\f0\b0  in the context of their importance calculations. This specific reference refers to 
\f2\b conditional variable importance
\f0\b0 , a method designed to provide more reliable importance rankings when predictors are highly correlated.\cb1 \
\ls14\ilvl0
\f2\b \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 Interpretive Limitation:
\f0\b0  They noted that because drivers covary, the model identifies variables that 
\f3\i explain
\f0\i0  the variance in spatial distributions, but these "apparent" sensitivities result from a combination of chemistry, physiology, and ecology
\fs28 \
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\sa120\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf4 \cb1 \strokec4 9. Sensitivity / interpretability analysis\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \strokec2 The study by Jin et al. (2024) utilizes several diagnostic techniques to interpret the Random Forest (RF) models and define the sensitivity of particulate carbon to environmental drivers.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs28 \cf0 Definition of Sensitivity\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 The researchers define sensitivity through 
\f2\b \'93apparent relationships.\'94
\f0\b0  These represent how the spatial distributions of PIC and POC respond to environmental fields that covary with them in a complex natural environment. The study distinguishes these from 
\f2\b \'93intrinsic physiological relationships,\'94
\f0\b0  which are typically found in controlled laboratory settings where only one variable is changed at a time. In this context, sensitivity refers to the identified impact a predictor has on the large-scale spatiotemporal distribution of the carbon pools.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs28 \cf0 Interpretability Diagnostics\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 The study employs three primary diagnostics to analyze these sensitivities:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls15\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Partial Dependence Sensitivity Analysis (PDPs):
\f0\b0  The authors use PDPs to visualize the 
\f2\b nonlinear response
\f0\b0  of PIC and POC to individual environmental parameters across their observed range. These plots (Figure 3) allow for a direct comparison of how the two carbon pools react to the same driver.\
\ls15\ilvl0
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Median Replacement Method:
\f0\b0  To examine spatial and temporal impacts, the researchers calculated the difference between a standard RF prediction (all variables at observed values) and a prediction where one variable was 
\f2\b replaced by its global median
\f0\b0 . This diagnostic helps map where and when specific variables, such as iron or light, most strongly influence biomass.\
\ls15\ilvl0
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Permutation Importance:
\f0\b0  This was used to rank the underlying determinants of variability. It is defined as the increase in error (RMSE) when a variable is permuted in the testing data set, normalized by the standard deviation of the target data.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs28 \cf0 Examination of Interactions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 The study explicitly acknowledges that the observed sensitivities are a result of 
\f2\b interactions between chemistry, physiology, and ecology
\f0\b0 . Specifically:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls16\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Ecological Interactions:
\f0\b0  The authors discuss how differences in sensitivity might suggest varying 
\f2\b grazing dynamics
\f0\b0 ; for example, an increase in non-PIC producers could lead to higher grazing pressure on PIC producers if they share common grazers.\
\ls16\ilvl0
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Biological Competition:
\f0\b0  They note that opposite-direction sensitivities could be attributed to 
\f2\b competition between functional groups
\f0\b0 , such as calcifiers and diatoms, particularly in polar regions.\
\ls16\ilvl0
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Environmental Modulation:
\f0\b0  The model includes variables like 
\f2\b mixed layer depth
\f0\b0 , which is noted to modulate both light supply and grazing pressure simultaneously.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs28 \cf0 Reporting of Uncertainty\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 While the study emphasizes the 
\f2\b robustness
\f0\b0  of the RF technique and its resilience against overfitting due to its ensemble nature (building trees on different subsets of data), the provided sources 
\f2\b do not explicitly report numerical uncertainty or confidence intervals
\f0\b0  around the sensitivity estimates in the main figures. The partial dependence plots and median replacement maps represent the mean behavior or impact derived from the aggregate result of the decision trees.\
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\sa120\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \strokec4 10. Transformations and scaling\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \strokec2 The study by Jin et al. (2024) utilized the following transformations and scaling methods:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls17\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Log Transforms:
\f0\b0  The target variables, 
\f2\b particulate inorganic carbon (PIC) and particulate organic carbon (POC)
\f0\b0 , were 
\f2\b log10-transformed
\f0\b0 . This transformation was applied to the target data sets before training the Random Forest models to handle the wide range of concentrations and enhance contrast in spatial distributions. Additionally, in the partial dependence sensitivity analyses, the predictors 
\f2\b mixed layer depth and dissolved iron
\f0\b0  were plotted on a 
\f2\b log scale
\f0\b0 , while all other environmental drivers were analyzed on a linear scale.\
\ls17\ilvl0
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Standardization and Normalization:
\f0\b0  To allow for a direct comparison between the PIC and POC models, the researchers 
\f2\b normalized the variable importance
\f0\b0  metrics. Specifically, the permutation importance (defined by the root mean squared error, or RMSE) was divided by the 
\f2\b standard deviation of the target data
\f0\b0  from each respective data set.\
\ls17\ilvl0
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Compositional Handling of Ratios:
\f0\b0  While the study emphasizes that the 
\f2\b ratio between PIC and POC
\f0\b0  is critically important for oceanic carbon storage, the modeling approach did not involve direct compositional handling of the ratio itself. Instead, the researchers 
\f2\b modeled PIC and POC independently
\f0\b0  using the same set of environmental predictors. This allowed them to compare the "apparent relationships" and sensitivities of each carbon pool to determine which drivers (such as light or iron) explain the differences in their respective global distributions.\
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\sa120\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \strokec4 11. performance metrics and scientific caveats \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \strokec2 The study by Jin et al. (2024) utilizes specific metrics and identifies several scientific caveats critical for interpreting their results.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs28 \cf0 Performance Metrics\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 The study focuses more on 
\f2\b variable importance and sensitivity
\f0\b0  than on traditional global model accuracy scores like $R^2$, although it notes that the Random Forest (RF) model can "robustly" relate carbon pools to environmental conditions.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls18\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Primary Metric:
\f0\b0  The researchers used 
\f2\b Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE)
\f0\b0  as the central metric for evaluating model behavior.\
\ls18\ilvl0
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Permutation Importance:
\f0\b0  Importance was defined as the increase in 
\f2\b RMSE
\f0\b0  generated when a variable in the testing data set was permuted while others remained at their observed values.\
\ls18\ilvl0
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Normalization:
\f0\b0  To allow comparison between PIC and POC models, the importance values were 
\f2\b normalized by the standard deviation of the target data
\f0\b0 .\
\ls18\ilvl0
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Reporting Scope:
\f0\b0  Performance and sensitivities were reported 
\f2\b globally
\f0\b0  through spatial maps and 
\f2\b zonally
\f0\b0  (by latitude) to capture seasonal climatological cycles. The authors specifically examined impacts in different regions, such as the 
\f2\b Southern Ocean, the Southeast Pacific, and the North Atlantic
\f0\b0 .\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs28 \cf0 \strokec2 Scientific Caveats and Limitations\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 The authors provide a detailed discussion of the limitations inherent in using machine learning to study ocean biogeochemistry:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls19\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Observational Bias:
\f0\b0  The study acknowledges that satellite-derived target data (PIC and POC) are subject to 
\f2\b algorithmic biases
\f0\b0 . For PIC, these biases can stem from high chlorophyll concentrations, the "package effect" (spatially varying relationships between backscatter and PIC), and the presence of sediments.\
\ls19\ilvl0
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Non-Causal Interpretation:
\f0\b0  A major caveat is the distinction between 
\f2\b "apparent relationships"
\f0\b0  and 
\f2\b "intrinsic physiological relationships"
\f0\b0 . The model identifies how carbon distributions covary with environmental fields in a complex natural system, which includes interactions between chemistry, physiology, and ecology. It does 
\f2\b not
\f0\b0  necessarily represent the direct, causal physiological growth rates found in controlled laboratory settings.\
\ls19\ilvl0
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Collinearity (Covariance):
\f0\b0  The researchers explicitly state that environmental drivers 
\f2\b covary
\f0\b0  in the ocean. To address this, they utilized 
\f2\b conditional variable importance
\f0\b0  (citing Strobl et al., 2008), which is designed to provide more reliable rankings when predictors are correlated.\
\ls19\ilvl0
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Domain and Range Dependence:
\f0\b0 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\ls19\ilvl1
\f2\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 High-Latitude Gaps:
\f0\b0  There is an "analytical gap" in 
\f2\b high-latitude regions during winter
\f0\b0  because passive satellite products cannot retrieve data in low-light conditions. The authors addressed this by filling gaps with the 1st percentile value, which may influence results in those specific domains.\
\ls19\ilvl1
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 pCO2 Range:
\f0\b0  The study found a negative relationship between carbon and CO2, which contradicts some previous studies. The authors suggest this may be due to the 
\f2\b specific contemporary range
\f0\b0  of pCO2 in their data set (325\'96407 ppmv), whereas older studies focused on lower historical concentrations where growth rates might respond differently.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls19\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Extrapolation Limits:
\f0\b0  The models are framed as tools to understand 
\f3\i observed
\f0\i0  distributions; the authors note that inaccuracies in simulating driving variables in Earth System Models (ESMs) can lead to poor simulation of these emerging relationships.\
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\sa120\partightenfactor0
